They have the appearance of having been made deliberately. Nine rivet holes: three down centre of hilt, three on each shoulder. The midrib of blade continues in the form of a pointed elevation up to the the lowest rivet hole in hilt. Edges of hilt are flanged, & two flanges run (from the top of hilt, nearly to its base) between the side flanges & the rivet holes. In addition two smaller flanges run between these two, for the distance between the uppermost rivet hole & the top of the hilt.
